ReportText: Chest, 2 views. History: Chest pain. Comparison: Chest radiographs dated 03/18/2007. Findings: PA and lateral views of the chest were obtained. The lungs are well expanded and clear. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The heart is normal in size. The aorta is normal. There are no acute osseous abnormalities. Impression: Normal chest. The films and dictation have been reviewed with the Resident and I agree with the findings.
